{{nihongo|'''Ogura Shrine'''|小倉神社}} is a [[Shinto shrine]] in {{ill|Ōyamazaki, Kyoto|ja|大山崎町}}, {{ill|Otokuni District, Kyoto|ja|乙訓郡}}, [[Kyoto Prefecture]]. It is listed as a major {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社}} and was formerly a {{ill|Gōsha|ja|郷社|qid=Q134917316}}.

== Enshrined deities ==
* {{ill|Takemikazuchi|ja|武甕槌神}}
* {{ill|Futsunushi|ja|経津主神}}
* {{ill|Ame-no-Koyane|ja|天児屋根}}
* {{ill|Himegami|ja|比売大神}}

== History ==
According to shrine tradition, the foundation dates to {{ill|Yōrō (era)|ja|養老|lt=Yōrō}} 2 ([[718]]). At the transfer to Heian-kyō, prayers were offered here to guard the imperial palace’s {{ill|kimon|ja|鬼門}} (“demon gate”). It is said the shrine received the Senior First Rank in Kajō 3 (850), though this is not recorded in {{ill|Nihon Montoku Tennō Jitsuroku|ja|日本文徳天皇実録}}. In the {{ill|Engishiki|ja|延喜式}} register ({{ill|Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳}}) it is listed as “Yamashiro Province, Otokuni District: Ogura Shrine (major), for the monthly and Niiname rites.”

During the {{ill|Azuchi–Momoyama period|ja|安土桃山時代}}, at the {{ill|Battle of Yamazaki|ja|山崎の戦い}}, [[Toyotomi Hideyoshi]] sent retainers [[:en:Katagiri_Katsumoto|Katagiri Katsumoto]] and [[:en:Wakisaka_Yasuharu|Wakisaka Yasuharu]] to pray for victory; thereafter a yearly offering of 3,000 ''hyō'' of rice was made. In the [[Edo period]], the [[Tokugawa shogunate]] granted over twenty ''chō'' of mountain land, and by the [[Meiji Restoration]] the former precincts totaled over 60,000 ''tsubo''.

Designated a village shrine (村社) in Meiji 6 (1873), it was promoted to {{ill|Gōsha|ja|郷社|qid=Q134917316}} in Meiji 16 (1883).

== Precincts ==
<gallery>
File:Oguta Jinja Oyamazaki Honden.jpg|Honden
File:Oguta Jinja Oyamazaki Katsuhaiden.jpg|Katsu-haiden (split/de­tached worship hall)
File:Oguta Jinja Oyamazaki Shinboku.jpg|Sacred tree (御神木)
File:Oguta_Jinja_Oyamazaki_Torii.jpg|First torii
</gallery>

== Access ==
* About 15 minutes’ walk west from [[:en:Nishiyama_Tennozan_Station|Nishiyama-Tennōzan Station]] on the [[:en:Hankyu_Kyoto_Main_Line|Hankyu Kyoto Main Line]].
* About 6 minutes’ walk from the Hankyu Bus stop “Daini Ōyamazaki Elementary School-mae.”

